{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place kale and water in mixing bowl then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Drain through a colander and refresh under cold water. Squeeze out any excess water then return to mixing bowl. Blend <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b> then scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sugar, eggs and almond extract then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add flour, baking powder and reserved chopped almonds then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 3<b>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula.","Flour prepared baking tray then tip sticky dough out onto it. Divide into two, then shape each piece of dough into a log shape (approx. 20 cm x 6 cm) - see tip.","Bake for 20 minutes (180°C). Remove from oven and allow to cool for 5 minutes.","Transfer log to a chopping board then use a serrated bread knife to cut in slices (1.5 cm wide). Arrange slices, flat side down, on baking tray then bake for 5 minutes (180°C) on each side. Transfer biscuits to a wire rack and allow to cool.","Serve, or store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g blanched almonds","60 g kale, thick stalks removed","30 g water","100 g caster sugar","2 large eggs","1 tsp natural almond extract","250 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","½ tsp baking powder"]}],"id":"r143329","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-RnSr_Dr-Cfk\/XZWrfzYUimI\/AAAAAAAAfoM\/cKG9-SS8KHU0Pf5W6j7rVtHvgSjHpz5ggCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nUEr4PVLWJ_v3uEQ.png","title":"Kale Biscotti","publishedAt":"2017-03-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.4 g","fat":"5.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19.3 g","calories":"604 kJ \/ 144 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, tongs, chopping board, wire rack, bread knife, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Biscotti will keep for up to 1 month if stored in an airtight container.","If the dough is very sticky, use wet hands to help shape it."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","16 pieces"]}